caption: Best spot keep up the good work
I've been coming here with my parents since I was a little girl(since the early 90s). The food is great!
Used to go there a lot.  Quality seems to have slid.  No reason to go back.

Ordered Kalamata Chicken dinners as a "THANK YOU"treat for the hard working staff in my building (showing up EVERY DAY during this time of COVID). I couldn't have asked for better food/service and assistance in doing so.  I called the night before to see how to coordinate it and was assured that all I had to do was call when they opened the next day.  I did and was told I could pick up 8 dinners within a half an hour⁉⁉⁉⁉ Meg/Megan(?) - forgive me if I got that wrong.... could not have been nicer and had everything packaged and ready for pick up.  It was fresh and HOT and so well received by the staff‼ A couple of the guys recognized it right away and were thrilled.  As a full dinner with the chicken, fries and a side salad with bread, it works out as a better value than pizza.  Truly a WINNER, WINNER, CHICKEN DINNER!!!   Thank you AR for helping me to thank those who have kept us moving through all this mayhem. If any of you want to thank all the support people we know and see everyday who have to commute even though we have the privilege to WFH, please consider ordering take out from the Athenian Room.  The food is fabulous, the staff is fantastic, and the value tremendous!
An absolute staple. 10/10 for the $$ to portion ratio
Great Greek food here. I prefer their appetizers (Kopita).
The chicken is good and gyros but the owner is very nice
A favorite location for quality Greek food. Service treated us so nice. Food and atmosphere reminds me of Kansas City.
One of my top spots for greek food. Bring your hunger - portions are filling. Atmosphere is like a restaurant in Fort Worth I loved.

Food was good, but I was shorted 2 orders and didn’t notice til I got home. Called the restaurant and was told I would have a credit under my name. When I called a few weeks later I was told    they wouldn’t honor it and I was probably calling the wrong restaurant! Won’t be going there again.
Always the best Greek food!
Great spot to stop in for a quick bite to eat.

Very limited menu.....Im vegetarian and every restaurant has at least a couple of items ....we ask the waiter if she could substitue a couple of ingredienrs and refused.....so we order just a greek salad and fries and them implied that was not enough food for me my party of three....the place is tiny the bathrooms were gross and was very hard to try to get to the stals.....I would never go back, ok if you eat chicken and giros...I guess, but I dont....one star because I could not give them cero stars

I have been going to AR for several years.  Growing up on the Northside of Chicago you begin to develop a list of favorite places to eat.  In high school, I appreciated the gyro plate at AR, especially because of the side salad that accompanies it.  I could enjoy that dressing every day.  But the best plate in my opinion is the Roasted Chicken over crispy fries.  That plate is insane and one of the best things I've ever eaten.  The service is always efficient and friendly.  This is a must-visit place in Chicago.
My top scene for tasty Greek food. Very savory. The staff was very friendly and attentive. Food and atmosphere reminds me of Atlanta.
Good place for outdoor dining . Pet friendly patio.

It’s very funny to me to read reviews of Athenian that are less than stellar!  Athenian is a legend, rock star, gem and phenomenon of Lincoln Park that my husband and I have been frequenting since we started dating 38 years ago!  The major players in the room, the furniture and the ambience are all the same!  They haven’t changed a thing. Luckily, the food hasn’t changed either. Basically go there for the kalmata  chicken and drenched fries. The best anywhere! If you want to complain about this place, go somewhere else. The management isn’t interested and neither is the line of 50 regulars waiting to be seated! After 38 years, I haven’t received even a free soda, but I keep showing up cuz the CHICKEN is the best!!  Hope they stay open with Covid!
Average eats - but big portions.
Been coming here since my kids were little. My husband's family has been coming since they were little. My parents use to have dates here. Great family tradition that connects both families
Simply oustanding!
Greek food and the atmosphere here is better than most. Looking forward to returning with my relatives. The bill was average for the menu. Ambience reminds me of Colorado Springs area.
Been here many times. Excellent food. Occasionally the service is subpar but it's usually pretty good.
The food is beyond delicious! Wish I could go back there!
This is the best restaurant of all time. Order the Kalamata Chicken.
Great place for delicious greek food. Staff is always super even when they have a full house. It has a cool atmosphere.
greek food at this place - super tasty. Two thumbs up for this place. I look forward to a return trip. Feels similar to a cafe in Chicago I liked.
Nice place for tasty Greek food. Super place to meet and chat with coworkers. Service is typically good. Prices were average for the menu.
Love this place! Always great food and a hidden Lincoln Park gem. Gyros are on point and so is their kalamata chicken.
Yummy gyro meat but it’s a big portion to only be giving one pita bread lol I bought another one anyways.
Love this place! Consistently good service, big portions and friendly staff! Thank you guys.
Nice patio.  Good service.

I dined at Athenian Room plenty of times in the past and had nothing but great experiences. However today, I was rudely greeted by the host staff who gave me a dirty look and appeared upset. Then, I was told that they are only accepting cash as payment. (Absurd since many restaurants switched to cashless payments). What really pivoted the situation is when the host told me that I couldn’t bring in my grocery bag that had two wine bottles in it (assuming that my intentions were to open the wine bottles I just bought at the grocery store). Absolutely ridiculous and unsettling. Finally, when I mentioned that on Groupon the restaurant mentions that they are BYOB, the host quickly dismissed me and didn’t offer me any room to speak. I will never dine in here again!

Skirt steak Alexandros style cooked to perfection! Greek fries, taramousalata, feta cheese, and soup are favorite add-ons. Get cream of chicken rice when in season and douse it with fresh lemon juice. Spread  taramousalata on bread and dip that in the steaks' plentiful juice. Crazy delicious!! 😋

The worst food ever. Extremely salty gyros and the fries were not fresh. This was a carry-out, so I called the restaurant and spoke with the 'manager'. She had initially taken my order and was the cashier for my bill. I explained that I was just there ordering the food. I said that the food was so salty that my blood pressure spiked, and that I'd like to return the food. (this was about 2 months ago). The manager said that it was alright, the she was 'sorry about the food' and that she would return my money (credit my card). Never happened. Thieves.

God do I crave this place when I leave Chicago.  Best Gyros Platter and Greek Chicken in the business. Always my first stop when I get home from traveling for work. Going for 20 years and will keep coming back again and again.
Skip it. Better food elsewhere for half the price
Rude staff. Average food
Great food
Great
Great service and on the weekends get carryout and save the headache of waiting for a table.
The absolute best. Big portions. Fresh food. The feta cheese is delicious. Overall, dining in is the best experience, but take our travels well too. Often busy, but always worth the wait.
Generous portions and always excellent billof fare!!!
This small restaurant has some yummy greek food. The greek salad with chicken was perfect for dinner and very cheap. It’s really similar with the restaurants in europe.
.. just amazing. DELICIOUS! Best meal I have had in Chicago so far. The price is also super low for the amount of delicious food i received. Thanks!

This was not our first visit but the first one in several years.  Service was prompt and attentive.  The Kalamatta chicken was good but a bit over cooked.  Crispy skin and a good sauce.  The taramasalta(sp) was mediocre.  Good bread and good pitas.  The gyros and tzatziki were just average.  We didn't have any of the burgers on this visit.  The price point was also good.  We will go back for another visit.
What’s better than a Greek salad with fries on top, grilled pita on the side and a slab of feta? N o t h i n g. This place slaps as a cheap summer spot. Please please visit.
The Athenian Room is a cozy, charming establishment with the best Greek food in the city at reasonable prices.
My first time here,  ordered take out. Gyro was REALLY dry & ended up throwing it out. Nice guy working counter, he gave my 2 year old Son a piece of baklava that was  really good.

Intimate, dimly lit and maybe just a tad noisey. Haven't had too mucj trouble finding parking yet.  I come for the steak Alexandros. A flank steak over a tangy sauce, served with fries and a salad with feta. I hear their burgers are good too.
Be ready to brawl with the patrons from Spartan Room. The press doesn't report what goes on because it's just too entertaining and ultimately insignificant.
It's fine. Literally just fine And the Stuff it’s not Professional
Greek food slaps!!

It's fine. Literally just fine. The Greek salad is boring and just lettuce with some sliced not-very-good tomatoes and cucumbers. The feta add-on is not great. Chicken and pork kebabs are...fine. I mean, look, this place isn't great, but the Greek food in Chicago is generally poor, so the bar isn't very high. If you've never had Greek food before, cool, have fun here. If you have had Greek food before and it's been Pita Xpress or something like that, this place will seem like it's great. But if you've had good Greek food...just keep your expectations low and you'll enjoy.

I have been coming here for years. Their Chicken Pita is incredible. Perfectly cooked every time and wrapped in a warm, fluffy pita. Tzatziki is the best in the city, which is saying something. Gyros are deliciously succulent and flavorful. Baklava is sweet and crunchy, just perfect. Their fries. Oh my god the fries. Fluffy on the inside, crispy on the outside, and covered in tangy vinegar and Greek oregano. Going here is like getting a warm hug from a beloved grandparent. Never change.
Wait times are long but it's worth it.  The best gyros and fries.  The chicken is unreal and the prices are amazing.  Just go with the host.  You may have to wait 20-25 minutes but it's worth it.
This place is a classic. Their menu is limited but EVERYTHING is fresh, delicious and very reasonable. If you want a drink, just grab one at the adjoined bar and bring it to your table.

My wife swore this place had the best Greek food around. I'm picky when it comes to my gyros, and Athenian Room did not disappoint. Hands down best Greek food around. Staff is fast, nice, and personable. Nice atmosphere too.
Nice
Great food, Great service and I love the atmosphere.
My mouth is salivating just thinking about the Greek chicken. You have to try it, it’s hard to describe the crispy skin and tender chicken, wow. I’d die for this chicken. Please go
Great food and great place!

Fantastic experience! Not only was the food super reasonably-priced and delicious, the service was excellent. The chef even gave us a baklava on the house! The atmosphere was very calm and quiet. Would highly recommend!
Pretty great!
Great!

I have been coming to the Athenian Room since 1987. I started eating there as a graduate student in Chicago and have been eating there ever since. I live in Cleveland now and I eat there every chance I get. For the last 15 years, I spend one weekend every summer with high school friends in Chicago. We play beach volleyball, run, go to Cubs games, kayak, attend summer fairs, drink at different bars and more. The one constant is our night at the Athenian Room. The gyro dinner, chicken, fries, salads are all fantastic. Analeese, has been our smiling, warm hostess since the 1980's. If you live in or come to Chicago, don't miss this place.
Loved it great place. Awsome greek food and decent prices
Very very good, basic Greek place.
Best Greek food in Lincoln park
Food is amazing and customer service is great..
Half of the chicken is juicy, half of it is dry. It's cheap, what can I say...
The wine steak is ok...thats what there famous for
A must for great affordable Greek food
Sorry to say it's not like it used to be
Best Greek restaurant in the USA!!!

Never. Just never go here.  Slow and horrible service. My entire meal and plate were coated/sitting in a quarter inch of olive oil.  Took forever to get check and pay with 25% full restaurant and half their staff standing around twiddling their thumbs.
Great food in Lincoln Park at reasonable prices.  Greek salad is excellent and gyros are juicy and flavorful.

I can't believe how this got a 4+ rating. Junk food that is dry, tasteless, overcooked and smothered in vinegar. A Greek would be embarrassed to be associated with this food. Only topped by rude staff, a family of Mexicans were trying to organise tables to make a bit of room and the lady manager/owner said 'you people' always want more! If I had been them I would have taken my business elsewhere!

This is my favorite store in Chicago. The service it is just great, they have and Ecuador coffee, the best sandwiches in Chicago, wine and cheeses ... everything is really tasty. Everyone should stop and support a local store with great products.
Great Gyros, Spinach pie with 2 types of fries.
Yummy!!!
Quick service with really delicious food
Always consistent and delicious!
It was great.
Good food and service.  Gyros sandwiches arr sometimes "pre-made" during busy times.

This place is a staple in Lincoln Park. Great greek food, very affordable. There's outdoor seating. They don't serve alcohol but you can order alcohol from Glascotts which is the bar that's attached to it. You can even order food directly inside Glascotts. MAKE SURE TO GET THE TARIMOSALA!! You won't regret it, it's amazing.
Got takeout here, it was just okay. Gyros were decent but dry and the sauce was too thick to easily put on. Fries were very soggy - didn't hold up well on the go. The baklava was great though.
Hey the Greek fries and in the winter don’t skip on the lemon rice soup

We came here after hearing Tina Fey talk about this place on Letterman's Netflix show. She did not lead us astray! The chicken on fries is so flavorful and the skirt steak is even better! So juicy!  There was a wait for dining in the restaurant so the hostess offered to seat us next door in the bar. It was so loud over there, I would not recommend this.  We will definitely be back!!
Great local greek food spot!
Not as good as it used to be. No saganaki...i could have sworn they used to have it.
Yummy everything!
Place used to be much better. Food is gone downhill somewhat. Service is great!
The taramosalata, the chicken, the steak, the kabobs, the fries...all so good.
Excellent food, good service, surprisingly cheap. Nice outdoor seating too
Great Steak and chicken dinners with fries and a salad. A lincoln Park institution. Gyros are homemade, better than Greek town.

This is one of the best old Greek restaurants in the city in my opinion. It's a small restaurant that doesn't serve alcohol but it is attached to a local bar and you can bring your drinks over. The gyros are absolutely delicious along with the Grecian chicken. There are many other menu items like kabobs and burgers that are also very very good. The wait staff is friendly and there's always an owner on hand.  During the warmer months they have outdoor seating.
Staff was friendly and helpful, food was ok... This place is more like a cafetería ... It is more like a fast food place.
EVERYTHING from the waitstaff to the food!
Good Greek feta burgers
Attentive staff.  The food (baked chicken, fries, and simple salad, akk in the same amazing dressing) is simple but awesome.  They do one thing but do it perfectly
Always fantastic
The food is very good  the chicken is one of the best in Chicago I loved
Best kalamata chicken ever!
Always good always amazing. 🇬🇷🇬🇷🇬🇷

Great food

Food was good. However, while we were eating the waitress came and gave us the tab when we weren’t even half way done eating. There were two white women sitting next to us who had been there before we even got there eating and they weren’t brought the tab at all. It was obvious they were trying to get rid of us as soon as they could. Definitely not coming back here; I won’t Support a place that discriminates me over the color of my skin or whatever the reason was.
I love going there whenever I get time and never disappointed with service and food. They have good selection of food but they are very busy during peak hours.
Delicious salad served with fries on top. Sounds strange but really good! Loved the outdoor dining option.
Authentic, classic Greek dishes, speedy service. The gyros is as it should be. The only improvement that is needed is more cucumber in the tzatziki sauce.
The food was amazing and such a great price point.
Excellent Greek food!!! Last time I had Greek chicken dinner perfectly cooked with Greek fries. So good! Outside seating and valet parking option. Owners are the best they'll take care of you. Oopah!
No frills Greek spot with great service and excellent food. They do not serve alcohol but you can go to the bar next door and bring back drinks.

Everyone has raved about this place since we moved in.  It was not what I expected. Very casual, somewhat limited menu. Evrything tasted great, and prices were super reasonable.  We'll definitely visit again, but it'll be a lunch or fast dinner type event.
Great food!
Love the Greek chicken and roasted potatoes to die for.
Only visited once and the food was really good. Definitely a second visit.. Weather permitting done alfresco..
Awesome waiter. Chicken Kalamata was crazy amazing.
Tasty Greek food with attentive staff...

Our daughter loves the way the 1/2 chicken is prepared here. My wife and I go for the skirt steak and fries. Our son?  Well, he loves the gyros piled up on his plate.  Yep.  We'll keep coming back here.  It's a nice spot for a family of 4 to reconnect after a long work week.
Good Greek food, comparable prices. Clean. When salad is ordered,  oil and vinegar is the only salad dressing option, a bit to much vinegar. Clean restrooms.
If you grew up in Lincoln Park area you had this at least once a month....such great food. So consistent. Love this spot
Delicious food
A Chicago classic.  Been coming here over 40 years.  Love it!

I don't even know if my compliments or remarks about the excellent doing experience we had at The Athenian Room will justify this establishment or the moment, but this remains the finest chicken dish (and feta cheese on the side) that we've had to date in this country.  Whatever they do to get the flavor and crispness of this lemon herb chicken needs to be written down, framed and displayed at the Smithsonian, it's an achievement and I can't get this meal out of my head. I've been through countless recipes and none come close to the utter peace that The Athenian Room sells in every bite.  Eat here and be haunted by it, find a good summer day and eat outdoors or a nice evening with good company and have your meal indoors, it should be compulsory, but use your willpower and make this decision.
Good food, great service, true Greek vibe and reasonable prices! Try the outdoor tables when the weather is nice.

Amazing food, dine in or out. Great prices and attached bar you can go and grab drinks from. I eat here regularly. The classic is the kalamata chicken dinner (comes with salad and get the feta), feta burger sub bread for pita and the sauce they serve the strip steak in is unbeatable.
great place, terrible website

Our family has been coming to Athenian Room for years. It never fails to please... I may be crazy, but I love their cheeseburgers (Feta and American) best of all! Greek Fries, Greek Salads, Chicken Kalamata, Skirt Steak Shish Kabob salad. Love it Love it Love it!! Do not miss this place if your in the neighborhood.
Get the chicken! It's awesomeness on a plate!
I've been eating here since a small child. Always wonderful food.
One of my top places for greek food. Staff is always timely even when they have a full house. Looking forward to a return trip. It has a good feel to it.
The best Greek food in the city
Food poisoning after eating at this place.  Dont get tricked with how nice the restaurant looks inside. Food was yummy but definitely not clean.
Can't speak highly enough of this place. Hasn't changed a bit in 20 years . Super delicious chicken don't pass it up !

Athenian is the gold standard of dining in Chicago. There is no better combination of value, quality of food, and ambiance. I’ve been eating here nearly weekly for the last five years, hesitant to write this review because I don’t want more people to bump me down the waiting list. This place is the goat
The Kalamata Chicken is one of my new top favorite dishes. Rotisserie chicken with lemon herb seasoning plopped on a bed of steak fries to soak in all the juice, brilliant.
I ordered for pick up half chicken,  I missed the salad, bread, and fork and napkin, The chicken is good
Good Greek food. Popular neighborhood spot. Large portions.  Only negative was that chicken was a bit dry.
The best Greek chicken ever. EV ER.
Food is good, ordered chicken Shish Kabab, the best part is actually the vinegar-ish sauce combined with potato. Very busy on Saturday night.
This place has my heart! Nothing like sitting outside in the summertime with a plate of chicken kabobs!

I really wanted to like this place but should have known to walk out as soon as we were seated and our drink orders almost finished being ordered before being told "no free refills"......what? We were seated in what seemed to be an employee area where everyone was milling about doing not much and staring at us. As we watched one half a dozen employees eat and the other half dozen chit chat. We did notice the food looking good and large portions, so I had high hopes. My GF ordered the Gyro Plate w/Greek fries, it looked great but the fries were in a pool of vinaigrette? So by the time she constructed her own gyro and remove the pile of meat most of the fries were soggy and sour. My super gyro lacked a super amount of onions needed for a super gyro. Only 4 small wedges of tomatoes and no cucumbers? The gyro meat and tzatziki had absolutely no flavor (no salt?) I was afraid to ask for extra onions as I expected to be charged extra for them. Our friend order the Greek fries but also plain fries and the greek burger. He enjoyed everything but still had an exorbitant about of vinaigrette on his plate, I dipped my Gyro in it to salvage the $10 sandwich. The baklava was dry, below standard and nothing to brag about. Also this is not a big deal but there is no alcohol at this establishment, FYI, not sure if it's BYOB? I rarely leave a bad review for restaurants but the fact that this place has been around since 1972 is mind boggling. The Greek chicken and kabobs might be a better route for dining. Order the Greek fries with the sauce on the side is a must and avoid the Gyro entirely.
classic
The food was delicious and the gentleman at the takeout counter was extremely kind!! Tina Fey mentioned this restaurant in an interview and she wasn’t wrong. The food is seriously good
Cozy restaurant with AMAZING greek food.
The food is average. The prices are low. Super crowded and you have to go next door to the smelly dive bar with a horrible wine list and carry your drinks over. I will never go back.
Always meets my expectations
Excellent Greek chicken!

The owner is EXTREMELY rude. She yelled at my brother and called postmates on him and LIED. He was having a bad day after he lost his wallet and informed her of that and she was completely disrespectful and was still yelling at him. I see why it took someone 2 HOURS to deliver an order from her. DO NOT BUY FROM HERE.
Great atmosphere and delicious food (especially loved the chicken and fries).  Can go next door and have a drink while waiting!
One of my favorite chicago spots. Get the Greek fries!
Love this place!  Athenian chicken is the bomb!😊
Food was all right, not that great but the service was something clearly special. The atmosphere was pretty cozy also.
Great spot in Lincoln park! The skirt steak is amazing!!!
Standard fare. The stand out of our meal was the baklava which was perfectly delicious. Perhaps the best I've ever had.

Kind of gamey Gyros meat. Good service. OK prices.
Service was great, had to go into bar to take kids to bathroom and no changing table.  Food was ok, good servings.  Also had to go to bar if anyone wanted a cocktail.
My favorite Greek restaurant and eating here since 1983! Not a bad item on the menu.
Our "go to" restaurant for Greek food for eat-in and carry out. Usual fare is great, but burgers and Grecian chicken are spectacular as well.  Eat here!

Went with my wife. Ordered appetizer.  It was not fresh at all. When I checked prices, they were 35% higher than the menu on line. We left, very disappointed. I'm Greek and as I left I noticed not one Greek in the kitchen. Apparently left old country values quick and adopted the American ones.

Delicious food for reasonable prices! I highly recommend the chicken (it is a full chicken) on a bed of fries with vinegar. The steak is also really good, just a bit more expensive (as would be expected).
Good food and great service! Staff will work hard to make you feel at home
Can't beat it and the chicken Kalamata is AMAZING.
Best Greek food in the city. Hands down. Tina Fey chicken is to die for.

My best friend and I had dinner there tonight. It was just like old times from high school the food was still great, very tasteful. Service was exquisite and marvelous, our waitress was very polite and Catering.I even got a chance to see the two original owners. I've been eating their Greek chicken since 1996, famous for their Greek fries, they're definitely known for their famous lemon soup, and my gyro plate was so full of meat and onions I found myself indulging trying to eat all of my food but I couldnt. I had to take home the rest of my meal. I can't wait to visit the Athenian Room again in the near future I'm going to try to make sure I stop by a little more often. Thanks for the Memories and then remarkable experience.
So good! Best gyros and the Greek fries are amazing! Classic Greek restaurant with great service.
Whenever we are in Chicago this is a must stop. We have been going here for 30 plus years. It is amazing! Fries have to be extra wet!  Everything is amazing!!
Wonderful meal.
Still the best!
Best gyros, worth the wait

Grab a beer at Glascotts if there’s a wait. The door connects the two businesses, and they’ll come find you when your table is ready. Two appetizers, two entrees, salad, a side of feta and desert for $31 including tax.  Food is awesome! Chicken was moist and tasty. Gyro was huge.  Hard to beat. Definitely recommended
The best
One of my favorite go-to’s for a Greek salad. The staff is friendly and the food is dependable.
Great authentic foods wonderful polite service oh ueah Good Food!!!
Always a staple! Everything is delicious.
absolute best-in-class chicken and potatoes, anywhere in town
Abundant portions, delicious salads and gyros

A Lincoln Park classic.  Good most days, but food quality can vary, particularly when busy...

Always a delicious, affordable meal.  A Chicago staple chain for greek food.  Tina Fey's fav place when she was acting @ Second City.

Always busy! Really enjoy the staple chicken dish. The value is fantastic. It's a small thing, but the upcharge for feta, does bother me a bit. Great place for takeout or to sit and enjoy the patio. Connected to the bar next door for drinks, which is fun.
Best Greek chicken in town. Alex and company really have it down pat.

How can I even try to explain my love for Athenian room?! I have been going there for about 8 years since I lived above it for four years.  It never disappoints. The skirt steak is so insane I can’t even begin to explain the delishness of the juice and fry combo. Don’t listen to any of he negative reviews it’s not the place that is trendy or cool but it won’t disappoint.

This isn’t a real Greek restaurant because they don’t have cheese triangles and they only had one Greek dessert on the menu. The menu is small and the food portions are small. You could go here on a budget. They have outdoor seating but we were bothered by a lot of wasps and had to move inside. Other than that food was good.

(Translated by Google) Good Greek restaurant, I was not surprised by the dishes. Good meat but nothing more. Many people at the door at 7 p.m., allow around 30 minutes to wait for a group.  (Original) Bon restaurant Grecque, je n'ai pas été surpris par les plats. De la bonne viande mais sans plus. Beaucoup de monde a la porte à 19h, prévoir environ 30min d'attente pour un groupe.

Не принуждённая атмосфера как внутри , так и на улице. Внимательные официанты . Есть валет паркинг  сервис. Очень доступные цены. Я бы назвал это место по настоящему семейным местом.

I've been here few times and my reaction has always been Meh! The Greek chicken is good and the burgers are ok but nothing special and the appetizers are non existent ( stay away from fried shrimp, it's just a cheap frozen variety and very greasy, not worth the price and consumption ) and make sure to check your entree ( i found hair on my burger the last visit )
Gyros dinner, cannot go wrong. Excellent restaurant, good service, reliable staff. Classic decoration as you'd expect. Steady.
Get the half chicken in lemon sauce. Tastes like heaven.
Good food, pathetic service.  Waitress was so lethargic I felt I should have apologized for ordering food.  You worked hard for your money, spend it elsewhere where your patronage is appreciated.
Great gyros. Huge portions
Skirt steak is the bomb
Looking for gyros, salad and chicken?  Look no further.

Greek food with atmosphere. Delicious gyros, chicken and salad. Steak fries brushed with an amazing light sauce. Inside seating year round and outdoor curbside seating during summer. Used to be a great place. The past three to four years has been lackluster and my last experience last year won’t have me go back after almost 20 years of patronage. It was busy, but despite heavy flow I still expect proper service. That’s gone down dramatically. Their customer service has really let us down and has been making (consistently) for a less-than-adequate culinary experience. When I place an order and do not get what I ordered, and upon mentioning it, I am simply told that “the kitchen is swamped”... just is not good enough. Food is still good, but more scant than ever before. Char burger with cheese used to be a slab of cheese. Now, a thin slice. So, nothing to write home about anymore.
